          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="toast-rounded">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/toast/#toast-rounded"}>
              Rounded prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The rounded prop in the Phoenix LiveView toast component allows you to customize the border radius of the toast. By default, the rounded prop is set to <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>, meaning the toast will have a moderate border radius. You can modify this to one of the following values: <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>large</.custom_inline_code>, or <.custom_inline_code>extra_large</.custom_inline_code>. If you want to remove the border radius, you can use <.custom_inline_code>none</.custom_inline_code>. This flexibility allows you to control the look and feel of the toast to fit your application's design.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" code={@code_7}>
            <div class="mb-6 flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
