          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="toast-padding">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/toast/#toast-padding"}>
              Padding prop in Phoenix LiveView toast component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The padding in the Phoenix LiveView toast component provides various padding size options, including <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>large</.custom_inline_code>, and <.custom_inline_code>extra_large</.custom_inline_code>. These options define the amount of space between the content inside the toast and its edges, with increasing amounts of padding from
            <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>
            to <.custom_inline_code>extra_large</.custom_inline_code>. If no specific value is provided, the default padding is set to <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>, ensuring a balanced and consistent look for the component.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" code={@code_9}>
            <div class="mb-6 flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
