          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="toast-width">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/toast/#toast-width"}>
              Width prop
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The width prop in the Phoenix LiveView toast component allows developers to control the element's width, offering flexibility to fit various design requirements. It supports predefined values such as <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>large</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>extra_large</.custom_inline_code>, and <.custom_inline_code>full</.custom_inline_code>. Each of these options defines a different maximum width, with
            <.custom_inline_code>full</.custom_inline_code>
            allowing the toast to span the entire width of its container. If no specific value is provided, the default width is set to <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>, ensuring a balanced and consistent look. Additionally, custom width values can be applied by passing a string that defines the width class directly.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper code_class="text-xs" code={@code_10}>
            <div class="mb-6 flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
              <.button
                variant="outline"
